Preparing data

rm(list = ls()) 
path <- "/Users/ouyangfu/Dropbox"
setwd(path)                                                                 

gold <- read_csv("gld.csv") %>%                  # read SPDR gold daily data
        select(Date, `Adj Close`) %>%            # keep only "date" and "adj close" 
        rename(X = `Adj Close`) %>%              # rename "adj close" -> "Xd"
        mutate(l.X = lag(X, n = 1L),             # lag X
               R = log(X/l.X),                   # log return
               DX = X - l.X) %>%                 # 1st order difference in X
          filter(is.na(R) == 0) %>%              # remove missing value
          filter(Date >= "2011-01-01") %>%       # use 2012-2014 data 
          filter(Date <= "2011-12-31")

  geom_line(aes(y = X), size = 0.3, color = "dodgerblue3") +

ACF

rhoX <- acf(gold$X, plot = F, na.action = na.pass)
alpha <- 0.95
conf.lims <- c(-1,1)*qnorm((1 + alpha)/2)/sqrt(rhoX$n.used)

rhoX$acf %>% 
  as_tibble() %>% mutate(lags = 1:n()) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = lags, y = V1)) + scale_x_continuous(breaks = seq(0,41,4)) +
  geom_hline(yintercept = conf.lims, lty = 2, col = "blue") +
  labs(y = "ACF", x = "Lag", title = "Daily SPDR Gold Prices, 2011") +
  geom_segment(aes(xend = lags, yend = 0)) + geom_point(size = 1) +
  theme(axis.title = element_text(family = "serif"),
        plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, family = "serif")) +
  ylim(-0.1,1.05)
## Warning: Removed 1 rows containing missing values (geom_hline).

Residual analysis

Residual plot
res.DX.arma32 <- residuals(DX.arma32)
fit.DX.arma32 <- fitted(DX.arma32)

res.analysis <- data.frame(res = res.DX.arma32, 
                           yhat = fit.DX.arma32, 
                           t = c(1:length(fit.DX.arma32)))

# residual against time
res1 <- ggplot(res.analysis, aes(t)) +
  geom_line(aes(y = res), size = 0.3, color = "dodgerblue3") +
  labs(y = "Residuals", x ="Time",
       title = "ARIMA(3,1,2) Residuals") +    
  theme(axis.title = element_text(family = "serif"),
        plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, family = "serif"))
print(res1)

## residual against fitted values
res2 <- ggplot(res.analysis, aes(res.analysis$res, res.analysis$yhat)) + 
  geom_point(alpha = .5, size = 2, color = "dodgerblue3") + 
  labs(title = "ARIMA(3,1,2) Residuals against Fitted Values", 
       x = "Fitted Values", y = "Residuals") + 
  geom_smooth(method = "lm", level = 0.95, color = "violetred3") +        
  theme(axis.title = element_text(family = "serif"),
        plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, family = "serif"))
print(res2)

QQ plot
y <- quantile(res.analysis$res, c(0.25, 0.75), na.rm = T) 
x <- qnorm(c(0.25, 0.75))         
slope <- diff(y)/diff(x)             
int   <- y[1] - slope*x[1] 

qq <- ggplot(res.analysis, aes(sample = res)) +
  geom_qq(alpha = 0.5, size = 3, color = "dodgerblue3") +
  geom_abline(intercept=int, slope=slope, color = "darkred", size = 1) +
  labs(title = "QQ Plot of ARIMA(3,1,2) Residuals", 
       x = "Normal Quantile", y = "Quantile of Residuals") +
  theme(axis.title = element_text(family = "serif"),
        plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, family = "serif"))
print(qq)
